CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 17, 1963, pg. 1 reads: "Over 2,000 Join UNPC in Massive Pittsburgh Walk - Pretty Evelyn Stroud (flowered dress), employee of a local banking firm, took advantage of her lunch hour to join the pickets as they marched around the Duquesne Light Company Building on Monday. - Harris Photo."One of the protesters is carrying a sign that reads: "We Want To Work Too!".
TitMainTitle: Protesters wearing "Let's March" arm bands marching in front of Duquesne Light Company building, Downtown
